HINTS



  These hints are meant to help you if you get stuck.




  If you peek too soon, you're only hurting yourself.








  1) You can run `go help` to see the list of available Go commands








  2) `go help <tool> gives you even more information








  3) You can find lots of package documentation at https://golang.org








  4) The `io/ioutil` package has some useful functions for reading








  5) You can `fmt.Fprintf()` to an `http.ResponseWriter`








  6) You can freely convert []byte arrays to strings, using string(b)








  7) IF YOU'RE REALLY STUCK ... check answer/server.go




